  "body": "### Description\n\nIn narayana-lra extension we need to differ between resteasy reactive (RR) and resteasy classic (RC) REST client cases. It doesn't work with RR because two artifacts shipped by Narayana contain `META-INF/services/javax.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder` file that point to the RC ClientBuilder implementation. The correct serviceloader file is provided also by RR but the two provided from two narayana artifacts are loaded first and thus narayana-lra cannot be used with RR because it tried to find not loaded RC clientBuilder. This was proven working with this user configuration:\r\n\r\n```\r\nquarkus.class-loading.removed-resources.\"org.jboss.narayana.rts\\:narayana-lra\"=META-INF/services/javax.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder\r\nquarkus.class-loading.removed-resources.\"org.jboss.narayana.rts\\:lra-client\"=META-INF/services/javax.ws.rs.client.ClientBuilder\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith the current Quarkus capabilities I was able to remove these files from the narayana-lra extension from the built jar or native but it doesn't work in devmode. After discussion with @aloubyansky the best solution would be to add a new configuration property \"excluded-resources\" to the ApplicationModel so the extension can configure this directly.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nMentioned above.",
